# Internal Links Loop (Strict)

Follow this loop exactly for internal-link insertion tasks.

1. Create `temp_internal_links_checklist.txt` with one line per article:
   - Format: `- [ ] src/content/blog/<slug>.mdx`
2. Pick the first unchecked article.
3. Choose silo targets: max 4 links to `/blog/*` per article; remaining links to `/`, `/about/`, `/services/`, `/blog/`, `/categories/`, `/tags/`, `/contact/`, category/tag hubs.
4. Insert links only in **paragraph** prose (not headings, lists, or buttons).
5. At least **10** paragraph links; unique Hebrew anchor text per link; unique `href` per article.
6. Ban anchors matching: `קריאה פנימית`, `קריאה קשורה`, numbered generic series, `קישור פנימי`.
7. Do not use the standard 7-nav boilerplate paragraph (`כדי לבנות הקשר רחב` + home/about/services block).
8. All internal paths use trailing slashes (e.g. `/about/`).
9. Sync `internalLinks` frontmatter array to match every internal path used in body paragraphs.
10. Run `pnpm run content:audit` for this slug.
11. Mark article done.

Hard requirements:
- Minimum 10 paragraph links (schema target; Zod may still be min 7 until raised).
- Log: `[internal-links-loop] step N` or `ERROR`.
- Preserve frontmatter schema; never modify unrelated files.
